This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on adapting the behavior of a robot based on human demonstrations. The use of Gaussian processes also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves modeling and prediction, which are common themes in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of simulated examples and real-robot experiments suggests a possible computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
